Which of the following is an advantage of using PDO over MySQLi with PHP?

1 / 1 point

✔️PDO can be used for many other SQL-based databases and makes future migration easier. MySQLi can only be used with MySQL database.


PDO is available for Windows, MacOS, and Linux and MySQLi is only available for Linux.


PDO can retrieve data one row at a time and MySQLi cannot.


PDO is written in object-oriented style and MySQLi is not.


2.
Question 2
Using MySQLi, how do you close this database connection?

$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

1 / 1 point

$conn->closeConnection();


mysqli_close($conn);

$conn = null

✔️$conn->close();


3.
Question 3
Using PDO, how do you close this database connection?

$conn = new PDO("mysql:host=$servername;dbname=$dbname", $username, $password);

1 / 1 point

✔️$conn = null;

$conn->disconnect();

PDO::close($conn);

$conn->close();


